{{Quote|<nowiki />''Cor'ika'', we've got a hundred and fifty ''shabla'' contingency rules, everything from arresting the Chancellor if he goes gaga to reducing key allied worlds to slag if they switch sides&hellip;|[[Atin Skirata|RC-3222]], to [[Corr Skirata|RC-5108/8843]] and [[Jedi General/Legends|Jedi General]] [[Etain Tur-Mukan]]|<ref name="Order 66: A Republic Commando Novel">''[[Order 66: A Republic Commando Novel]]''</ref>}}
The '''Contingency Orders for the Grand Army of the Republic: Order Initiation, Orders 1 Through 150''' was a compilation of contingency orders that were to be carried out under various circumstances by the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]] (GAR).

==Known orders==
*[[Order 4]]: "In the event of the [[Supreme Commander (Republic)|Supreme Commander]] ([[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Chancellor]]) being incapacitated, overall GAR command shall fall to the [[Vice Chair/Legends|vice chair]] of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]] until a successor is appointed or alternative authority identified as outlined in Section 6 (iv)."<ref name="True Colors">''[[Republic Commando: True Colors]]''</ref>
*[[Order 5]]: "In the event of the Supreme Commander (Chancellor) being declared unfit to issue orders, as defined in Section 6 (ii), the [[Chief of Defense Staff|Chief of the Defense Staff]] shall assume GAR command and form a strategic cell of senior officers (see page 1173, para 4) until a successor is appointed or alternative authority identified."<ref name="True Colors" />
*[[Order 37]]: Capture of a single wanted individual through the mass arrest and threatened execution of a civilian population. Follow-up directives include scenarios for body disposal of civilian casualties and suppression of communications.
*[[Order 65/Legends|Order 65]]: "In the event of either (i) a majority in the Senate declaring the Supreme Commander (Chancellor) to be unfit to issue orders, or (ii) the [[Senate Security Council|Security Council]] declaring him or her to be unfit to issue orders, and an authenticated order being received by the GAR, [[Commander/Legends|commanders]] shall be authorized to detain the Supreme Commander, with lethal force if necessary, and command of the GAR shall fall to the acting Chancellor until a successor is appointed or alternative authority identified as outlined in Section 6 (iv)."<ref name="True Colors" />
*[[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]]: "In the event of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Officer/Legends|officers]] acting against the interests of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]], and after receiving specific orders verified as coming directly from the Supreme Commander (Chancellor), GAR commanders will remove those officers by lethal force, and command of the GAR will revert to the Supreme Commander (Chancellor) until a new command structure is established."<ref name="True Colors" />

One order called for the [[Base Delta Zero/Legends|Base Delta Zero]] of key Republic worlds in the event they joined the Separatists.<ref name="Order 66: A Republic Commando Novel" />

In addition to the known orders, in the aftermath of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Declaration of a New Order|rise]] to power, the newly christened [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] came to suspect that his [[Sith Master/Legends|master]], the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Sidious—known to [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] as the newly crowned [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]—had developed a new contingency order (Order 151) to eliminate him should the need arise. Lord Vader questioned [[Clone Commander/Legends|Clone Commander]] [[Vill]], referencing the contingency orders the [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] had known while a part of the Grand Army before the Republic's fall. When the officer indicated that he was unauthorized to confirm or deny the existence of any such order, Vader considered his suspicions confirmed and quickly [[Telekinesis/Legends|dispatched]] Vill so as not to alert the Emperor of his inquiry.<ref name="BlueHarvest3">[[Dark Times 15|''Dark Times'' 15]]</ref>

Although technically not part of the Contingency Orders for the Grand Army of the Republic due to it being used exclusively with the Separatists, a similarly named order called [[Order 99]] existed among its forces, which made the droids move to the opposing side. The order was developed as a test for the later Order 66 for the clone troopers to use against the Jedi.<ref name="The Only Good Clanker">{{TCWComicCite|6.26|The Only Good Clanker}}</ref>

